<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Please read my GAR Calculation post, it solves these issues</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:17 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Please read my GAR Calculation post, it solves these issues<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=312" TARGET=_self>Make the level limits even harsher</A> (Walter Mitty)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Any problem can be solved with a little analysis and some work on the part of the dev team :-)
<P>My GAR system will provide a flexible system for handling group PvP in Everquest. Feel free to shoot it full of holes and I'll do my best to patch it up.
<P>&gt; I've looked over the below posts, and don't think they work; the
<BR>&gt; best of the suggestions is the comparison of average levels, but
<BR>&gt; then the problems of level fifties grouped with level ones
<BR>&gt; arise. Comparing highest and lowest members fo groups sounds
<BR>&gt; good, but i'd prefer to stay away from anything that uses
<BR>&gt; different standards for attacker and attacked, as that can lead
<BR>&gt; to exploitation. (Otherwise it's very similar to what I
<BR>&gt; propose.)
<P>&gt; I also think anyone who's played the game realizes that level
<BR>&gt; limits are a necessity.
<P>&gt; So I propose this: make the limits apply more harshly. If anyone
<BR>&gt; in any given party is outside the level range of any member of
<BR>&gt; another party, those two parties simply cannot initiate PvP with
<BR>&gt; one another.
<BR>&gt; I realize this proposal won't be popular, because it prevents
<BR>&gt; PvP even more than the current system does; but there is no
<BR>&gt; other fair solution.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
